sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K575007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Continous expression of RhlR receptor protein (with RBS, B0034)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a Constitutive Promoter combined with RBS (B0034) and RhlR so that the cell continuously expresses RhlR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kristin Palarz
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: These parts come from the BioBrick Registry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The strength of the Constitutive promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K575023
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a promoter region extracted from the Pseudomonas Aeruginosa genome. It is activated by the PAI-2/RhlR complex, part of the Pseudomonas quorum sensing hierarchy.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Vincent Sherer
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is the upstream regulatory regions of (gene).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is unusually long for a promoter because of the primers we used to extract it. We do not know exactly where the regulatory region is.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
